-- S. Korea to Extend Tariff Cut on Crude for LPG Use Through June
-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 2012-01-05T07:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/s-korea-to-extend-tariff-cut-on-crude-for-lpg-use-through-june.html
South Korea  will extend its tariff
drop on crude oil used to make liquefied petroleum gas by six
months through June, according to a joint statement from the
finance and other ministries.  The 2 percent tariff on such imports has been dropped from
May to stabilize the local cost of heating fuel for low-income
residents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at   sihan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
